˘gan, 2011, described from Turkey (Dönel and Do ˘gan 2011), by smooth dorsal plates, three pairs of aggenital setae situated on single plate, presence of eyes. However, it differs from the latter by much longer dorsal body setae, absence of seta d on genu III (vs. present in
